This Is Trevor Gordon
The surfer video playlist and interview featuring @tearevor, a regular footer from Santa Barbara, California who lives with his wife on a sailboat.

🔗Link in bio/stories @nobody_surf

📼 Deepest Reaches For Mollusk 2014
Surfboard by Deepest Reaches (@deepestreaches)
Presented by Mollusk Surf Shop (@mollusksurfshop)
🎥 Michael Kew (@michael.kew)
🎵 "Yuba Diamond" by Sandy's (@sandysband)

#Surfing #NobodySurf

Watch “A high point” now! So fun hunting out subterranean tubes with the crew. Epic trip to a part of the world I hope to spend more time in someday! ⛵️🏝 Thanks for the fun @mollusksurfshop 

Footage from the hog @tygelanda 

Full film with @krooky and @brycebaker3 at link in my bio.

I made some stuff! Check out the link in my bio. Pretty darn limited run but have a poke!

TOY BOAT TRANSPORTATION

Video production thanks to @donnielloyd_ @erinfeinblatt and @yoderyoder and additional art @_toshyboy

Fun times in the dirt with 📹@nate_stephensonn  and @yewview 

@mollusksurfshop
@tearevor and @brycebaker3 heat up at J Bay in Mollusk Warm Wetsuits. Watch “Pure Energy” through the link in our bio

Fresh new batch of 4 TOYBOATS headed to @mollusksantabarbara

5’4”, 5’5”, 5’6” Flathead fishes and an 8’6” Lordship.

Thanks for the shaping filming @nate_stephensonn 
Surf clips @erinfeinblatt @tygelanda

Thank you so much @surfersjournal for including me in this awesome issue. Chuffed to bits… and so stoked on the other sailing stories in this one from @john_john_florence @torrenmartyn @a.i.yan.a  @rhinorudder… Such fun parallels between sailing and surfing and so refreshing to see in print. 

Thanks so much to everyone who put energy into this. 

To Ethan Stewart (@thelast3days) for the tasteful words and time spent!

To Morg (@morganmaassen) for inlcuding some classic lomo photos in there of and @dirtwax and I from our school-less hours lurking sandbar.

To Will Adler (@willadlerphotographs) for flying all over the world to take photos and put in a night shift. Spain, Panama and Baja. 

And to Erin Feinblatt (@erinfeinblatt) for working so damn hard. Not just taking photos but for the effort in general, down in the engine room or in the boat yard in Spain. Not sure how many days you spent sailin’ with me on this trip, a lot, I appreciate them all. Back cover photo was taken by Erin. Nearing Colon, Panama after a spicy 5 days and 900nm at sea from Dominican Republic.

And Maddie thanks for @mollusksurfshop for the support.

Wild hog hunting has been great lately. Thanks @jolewilson !! With freezers full and Maddie bouncing off the wall with recipes and cooking projects, the boat has been thoroughly warmed by the oven and bellies are full.

@maddiegordonart recently honed her skills in and has been focusing on a good old fashioned blog, where she shares old timey skills in and around the kitchen. From time to time we will share fishing and hunting stories that lead back to the galley on Aldora. With some recent success with an Arizona Mule deer, stay tuned for deer processing and recipes on the boat. 

For $6 a month you can subscribe to full access to all the stuff ❤️ link in bio. 

Tomorrow a big ol’ medeivel style pig pie comes up on the newsletter!

Thanks for the photos @nate_stephensonn !
